Content:: Teodoro Carlos Quintana (1950 – 13 July 2022) was an Argentine trade unionist and politician. A member of the Front for Victory within the Justicialist Party, he served in the Chamber of Deputies from 2005 to 2009.[1] Quintana died in Buenos Aires on 13 July 2022.[2] This article about an Argentine politician is a stub.
